Which of the following languages are undecidable? Note that $$\langle M\rangle $$ indicates encoding of the Turing machine M.
<br><br>L<sub>1</sub> = $$\left\{ {\langle M\rangle |L\left( M \right) = \phi } \right\}$$
<br>L<sub>2</sub> = $$\{ \langle M,w,q\rangle |$$ M on input w reaches state q in exactly 100 steps }
<br>L<sub>3</sub> = { $$\langle M\rangle |$$ L(M) is not recursive }
<br>L<sub>4</sub> = { $$\langle M\rangle |$$ L(M) contains at least 21 members }
